39,0.02191669,0.00962479,-0.00330004,0.01215755,0.01946078,0.04900293,-0.04880017,0.01619582,0.08482736,0.20614707,0.05796885,0.00180638,0.01837601,0.02148645,0.01364082,0.05192384,0.00328992,-0.03625738,0.00274082,0.06007681,-0.03625326,0.04125505,0.01807627,-0.03377652,-0.02419485,0.0575983,0.02710035,0.03131435,-0.02375033,0.06169783,0.02039029,0.09212908,-0.01302043,0.00581917,-0.06909392,0.02553029,0.01594227,-0.05111343,-0.01400289,0.01021519,0.01853755,0.00307083,0.12019005,0.01333311,-0.04499689,-0.01201917,-0.01918438,0.06831291,-0.09068155,0.09419891,0.00783756,0.0412325],"last_embed":{"tokens":418,"hash":"1p66xdu"}}},"last_read":{"hash":"1p66xdu","at":1782088669940},"class_name":"SmartSource","last_import":{"mtime":1782005162375,"size":11755,"at":1782088568887,"hash":"1p66xdu"},"blocks":{"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58":[1,63],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[feature] LLM Council Skill Implemented: The LLM Council skill has been implemented to enhance decision-making processes. This skill leverages a methodology adapted from Andrej Karpathy's LLM Council, employing five independent AI advisors. Each advisor approaches a query from a unique thinking lens: the Contrarian identifies flaws, the First Principles Thinker re-evaluates the core problem, the Expansionist seeks upside, and the Outsider offers an unbiased view. The skill is intended for complex questions where the cost of a wrong decision is high, providing a synthesized recommendation after peer review. It is triggered by phrases like \"council this\" or \"run the council\" and is not meant for simple factual lookups or basic creation tasks.":[3,4],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[bugfix] Mermaid-cli installation failed due to Puppeteer download error: An attempt to install `@mermaid-js/mermaid-cli` locally within the `/tmp/mmd-check` directory failed. The npm output indicates that the installation process encountered an error while trying to download the necessary browser binaries for Puppeteer, a dependency of `mermaid-cli`. The error trace points to issues within the Puppeteer installation script. A detailed debug log was created, which would likely contain more specific information about why the browser download failed (e.g., network issues, permissions, or corrupted cache).":[5,6],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[decision] TTS Integration Phase 33 Initial Implementation: The initial part of PHASE-33 (TTS Integration) is complete. The system now has a robust foundation for audio generation, featuring a provider-based architecture that allows for easy expansion. By using build tags, the audio capabilities remain optional, ensuring the binary stays lean for non-audio users. The implementation of Kokoro and Qwen3 as native providers (via Python subprocesses) bridges the gap between high-performance ML models and the Go runtime. The next critical steps involve integrating these capabilities into the Gateway and Channel adapters to enable actual voice delivery to users.":[7,8],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] JSON API SQL Quote Stripping Issue: During the attempt to fetch validation counts for the ARSESP volume, it was discovered that the JSON API strips SQL quotes, rendering the queries invalid. To bypass this limitation and ensure the integrity of the SQL statements, the workflow has shifted to writing the query to a temporary file and utilizing the readonly validator for execution.":[9,10],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Etraider Comprehensive System Architecture: The analysis of Etraider reveals a sophisticated \"Foundation\" layer designed for autonomous crypto trading. While the system has a robust architectural skeleton—including a real-time dashboard, a dedicated AI agent worker, and a shared type system—it is currently a signal-generation and analysis engine rather than a full trading bot. The separation of the API and Agent processes mirrors the conceptual split in OpenAlice, and the use of a shared type contract ensures consistency across the full stack.":[11,12],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[change] Local repository update from Databricks Workspace: The user requested to download the application files from a specific Databricks workspace path (/Workspace/Users/cs318364@comgas.com.br/databricks_apps/agent-corporativo) to their local machine to ensure the local repository is up-to-date with the remote environment.":[13,14],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[change] Strategic intent update: The user updated the session's strategic intent, indicating a plan to use the recently activated LLM Council skill to evaluate the status of 'claude-mem' and how agents are connecting.":[15,16],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Searching for 'Majoor' in Python Files: The agent is searching for the term 'Majoor' within the Python codebase. This appears to be a search for a specific identifier, username, or project-specific keyword that may be linked to the configuration or the user's environment, potentially helping to locate where specific paths or permissions are being managed.":[17,18],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[learning] Unique Pattern: Some insight":[19,20],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] System browsers and Brave Flatpak found: The system was checked for the presence of browsers that Puppeteer could potentially use. Google Chrome was found to be installed in two locations, and another executable named 'chrome' was also detected. Additionally, 'chrome-headless-shell' was found. The output also indicates that Brave browser is installed as a Flatpak. The absence of the `~/.cache/puppeteer` directory suggests that Puppeteer has not downloaded any browser binaries to this location, which aligns with the previous installation failure.":[21,22],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Ruflo not installed globally: The user asked a direct question regarding the installation scope of the 'ruflo' tool, specifically questioning why it was not installed globally within the observed Claude session's environment. This indicates a potential need for clarification on tool management or environment configuration.":[23,24],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Validator Output Limitation Persistence: Despite switching to a file-based execution method to avoid JSON API quote stripping, the validator tool still only confirms the success of the statement without returning the resulting data rows. This confirms a consistent limitation in the validator's output capabilities, necessitating a different approach to retrieve the actual counts for the ARSESP volume validation.":[25,26],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Etraider Component Location: During a search for specific UI components in the Etraider project, `draggable-card.tsx` was successfully located. The search for ZeroRepaintChart and EquityCurve is continuing with broader patterns as initial exact matches were not found.":[27,28],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Thoth Project Architecture Exploration: The user is initiating a comprehensive architectural review of the Thoth project. The focus is on understanding how the system handles audio and Text-to-Speech (TTS), specifically looking for tts_bridge.go and related task catalog entries. The investigation covers the end-to-end flow from the delivery request through the gateway and provider adapters to the final channel delivery (WhatsApp/Telegram), as well as the underlying build system and tool registration mechanisms.":[29,30],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[change] Local Environment Activation Request: The user has requested the activation of the local development environment for the corporate agent specifically to perform a visual verification of the layout.":[31,32],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Context gathering for LLM Council: Following the operational protocol of the `llm-council` skill, the agent is performing \"context enrichment\" by reading the project's `CLAUDE.md` file. This is a prerequisite step to frame the question accurately before convening the council of advisors.":[33,34],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Investigation of Smart Startup Script: Continuing the root cause investigation into the permission error, the agent is now analyzing `run_comfyui_smart.sh`. This script may contain more complex logic for determining mount points or environment variables than the standard startup script, making it a primary suspect for the source of the `/run/media/` vs `/media/` path discrepancy.":[35,36],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[learning] Padrão encontrado: Descobriu-se que...":[37,38],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[security_alert] Google client_secret hardcoded and compromised: The Google OAuth client_secret was found to be hardcoded directly within the application's source code. This poses a significant security risk, as it means the secret is exposed and should be considered compromised. A manual intervention is necessary to revoke the existing client_secret and generate a new one. This new secret must then be securely stored in the environment variables, specifically within the `.env` file under the key `GOOGLE_OAUTH_CLIENT_SECRET`.":[39,40],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Ruflo installation status confirmed: The command `which ruflo 2>/dev/null || echo \"NOT FOUND\"; npm list -g ruflo 2>/dev/null | head -5; ls ~/.npm/bin/ruflo 2>/dev/null || echo \"not in ~/.npm/bin\"` was executed to check the global installation status of ruflo. The output confirms that ruflo is installed within the Node Version Manager's directory (`/home/michel/.nvm/versions/node/v22.22.3/bin/ruflo`) and is listed as a global module for that Node version. However, it is not found in the `~/.npm/bin` directory, indicating it's not globally accessible in the way a user might expect from a standard global npm install.":[41,42],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] ARSESP Volume Post-Upload State: After resolving the timeout and API limitations, the post-upload validation confirms that the ARSESP volume has grown from ~217 to 717 files. With 5543 eligible registry entries still pending success and a significant increase in available files, the system has determined that generating new parse batches is the appropriate next step to process these candidates.":[43,44],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Etraider Component Absence: Following a search for specific UI components, it was discovered that while DraggableCard exists, the ZeroRepaint and EquityCurve components are currently absent from the Etraider project codebase.":[45,46],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[decision] TTS Integration Strategy: Hermes to Thoth: The project aims to fully integrate the Hermes TTS capabilities into Thoth. This involves moving away from the current HTTP bridge toward a native Go implementation. The architectural change requires updating the gateway delivery contracts to handle audio formats instead of just text, enabling voice responses on messaging platforms like WhatsApp and Telegram. The implementation will be gated by a build flag and include an automated voice model installation process.":[47,48],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[change] Configure Azure DevOps MCP Server: The user configured the Azure DevOps Model Context Protocol (MCP) server to enable integration with the ComgasIT organization. This allows the assistant to interact with Azure DevOps resources using the provided authentication token and organization endpoint.":[49,50],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Project Architecture and Agent Guidance: The `AGENTS.md` file provides a comprehensive map of the system's architecture. Crucially for the current strategic intent, it reveals that `apps/daemon` is responsible for agent spawning and skills, and that agent-specific working directories are stored under `.od/projects/<id>/`. This confirms the technical surface area that the LLM Council will need to analyze when evaluating 'claude-mem' status and agent connectivity.":[51,52],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[discovery] Investigation of Application Settings: As part of the effort to resolve the permission error caused by the path discrepancy between `/media/` and `/run/media/`, the agent is now inspecting `app_settings.py`. This file likely contains the default paths and configuration variables used by the application, which could be the source of the incorrect path reference.":[53,54],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[decision] Test: Content":[55,56],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[change] Clarification on dream_cycle testing configuration: A question was raised to clarify whether the `dream_cycle` tests, when utilizing a mocked LLM, are configured through the `./scripts/setup-dreamer.sh` script. This seeks to understand how the model configurations for these specific testing scenarios are managed.":[57,58],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[feature] Implement user logout functionality: A logout feature has been implemented, allowing users to securely end their sessions. The `/api/auth/logout` endpoint, protected by JWT authentication, invalidates the current user's token. This is achieved by adding the token to a blocklist, preventing its future use and effectively logging the user out.":[59,60],"#Sessão Episódica: 2026-06-20 11:58#[change] ARSESP Parse Batch Plan Generation: Following the validation of the ARSESP volume (now containing 717 files), the process has transitioned to generating a new parse batch plan. This plan will specifically target the next 20 eligible documents, creating the necessary SQL to identify them and trigger the `ai_parse_document` function for processing.":[61,63]},"outlinks":[],"task_lines":[],"tasks":{},"codeblock_ranges":[],"key":"cortex/parietal/inbox/2026/06/20/1158-session.md"},
